        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-2652",
        "content": "The cut, which is very rough, heads a bacchanalian ballad characteristic of the Elizabethan period, called \"A Knotte of Good Fellows,\" and beginning:",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-low_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "F",
